Which patient groups should be asked to participate in first-in-human trials of 
stem-cell-based therapies?

Hug K(1), Hermerén G.

Author information:
(1)Department of Medical Ethics, Faculty of Medicine, Lund University, Lund, 
Sweden. Kristina.Hug@med.lu.se

The aims of this article are to consider (1) whether there are medical and 
societal differences among diseases regarding which patient groups should be 
asked to participate in first-in-human (FIH) trials of stem-cell-based 
therapies; (2) any differences in the light of values generally endorsed by 
