common to several diseases. To illustrate these problems, we use Parkinson's 
disease (PD) and Huntington's disease (HD), between which there are important 
medical and societal differences. Moreover, research on stem-cell-based 
therapies for these diseases is being translated from research to practice. This 
approach to the problem can be applied to decision making about similar problems 
raised by other diseases that exhibit the same types of differences.

